        "contact": {
          "email": "feedback@data.gov.sg"
        },
        "description": "The UV Index API provides real-time data on ultraviolet index levels for various locations in Singapore. Users can retrieve the latest UV index information updated every hour between 7 AM and 7 PM. The API allows for filtering by date or datetime via query parameters.",
        "license": {
          "name": "Singapore Open Data Licence",
          "url": "https://data.gov.sg/open-data-licence"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://data.gov.sg/api/action"
          }
        ],
        "title": "UV Index API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Hourly UV index readings for Singapore from data.gov.sg, published between 7am and 7pm",
        "homepage": "https://data.gov.sg",
        "docs_url": "https://data.gov.sg/datasets",
        "license_short": "Singapore Open Data Licence",
        "license_md": "- Data is published under the **Singapore Open Data Licence** by the Government of Singapore.\n- Free to use, share, and adapt for any purpose, including commercial use.\n- Attribution to the source agency (data.gov.sg) is required.\n- Provided on an \"as-is\" basis; check the official terms at data.gov.sg before relying on it for critical applications.",
        "about_md": "The UV Index API exposes ultraviolet index readings for Singapore, served by [data.gov.sg](https://data.gov.sg), Singapore's official open data portal. Readings are produced from the National Environment Agency's monitoring network and surface as hourly values during daylight hours.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- Hourly UV index values published between 7am and 7pm local time\n- Filtering by `date` or `date_time` query parameters to fetch a specific window\n- A timestamped record per reading suitable for plotting trends or feeding alert thresholds\n\nThe underlying endpoint is hosted at `https://api-open.data.gov.sg/v2/real-time/api/uv`. CORS is enabled, and no API key or authentication is documented for this endpoint. Rate limits are not publicly stated, so be considerate when polling.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "uv_index": "Hourly ultraviolet index readings for Singapore, returned from the real-time UV endpoint (`/v2/real-time/api/uv`) with optional `date` or `date_time` filters."
        },
